nodes.bodyText:
The closer I look at it the more little things I see, sorry. But, cancelTask(TASK_TYPE) used to delegate to cancelTask, which just silently eats all Exceptions. Now you are cancelling the task directly so it's missing all this safety code:
        try {
            if ((sLatestInstance != null) && (sLatestInstance.getStatus() != AsyncTask.Status.FINISHED)) {
                sLatestInstance.cancel(true);
                Timber.i("Cancelled task %s", sLatestInstance.mType);
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return;
        }

the finished check
the logging that it's being cancelled
the exception catch

